.TH GOSENDMAIL 8 "April 2026" "gosendmail 1.0.0" "System Administration"
.SH NAME
gosendmail \- Modern Go backend for handling contact form submissions
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B gosendmail
[\fI\,OPTIONS\/\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B gosendmail
is a modern Go backend implementation that replaces traditional PHP contact form handlers. The application processes contact form submissions with validation, reCAPTCHA verification, and SMTP email sending.

The service runs as a background daemon and provides HTTP endpoints for processing contact form submissions from web applications.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-h, \-\-help\fR
Display usage information and exit.
.TP
\fB\-v, \-\-version\fR
Display version information and exit.
.TP
\fB\-c, \-\-config\fR \fIFILE\fR
Path to configuration file (default: /etc/gosendmail/config.yaml).
.SH CONFIGURATION
The service is configured through environment variables or a YAML configuration file.
Key configuration options include:
.TP
\fBRECAPTCHA_SECRET_KEY\fR
Google reCAPTCHA secret key (required).
.TP
\fBSMTP_HOST\fR
SMTP server hostname (required).
.TP
\fBSMTP_USERNAME\fR
SMTP authentication username (required).
.TP
\fBSMTP_PASSWORD\fR
SMTP authentication password (required).
.TP
\fBFROM_ADDRESS\fR
From email address (required).
.TP
\fBTO_ADDRESS\fR
Destination email address (required).
.TP
\fBSERVER_HOST\fR
Server bind address (default: 0.0.0.0).
.TP
\fBSERVER_PORT\fR
Server port (default: 8080).
.TP
\fBRATE_LIMIT_REQUESTS\fR
Rate limit per window (default: 10).
.TP
\fBRATE_LIMIT_WINDOW\fR
Rate limit time window (default: 1m).

For a complete list of configuration options, see the example configuration file at /etc/gosendmail/gosendmail.env.
.SH HTTP ENDPOINTS
The service provides the following HTTP endpoints:
.TP
\fBPOST /sendmail\fR
Legacy HTML endpoint compatible with traditional HTML forms (returns HTML responses).
.TP
\fBPOST /contact\fR
Modern JSON REST endpoint (returns JSON responses, recommended for new integrations).
.TP
\fBGET /health\fR
Health check endpoint for monitoring.
.SH FORM FIELDS
The contact form supports the following fields:
.TP
\fBfirstName\fR, \fBname\fR
Required, French letters/spaces/hyphens/apostrophes, max 64 chars.
.TP
\fBpostbox\fR
Optional, numbers only, max 5 chars.
.TP
\fBstreet\fR
Required, French letters/spaces/hyphens/apostrophes, max 128 chars.
.TP
\fBcity\fR
Required, French letters/spaces/hyphens/apostrophes, max 45 chars.
.TP
\fBzip\fR
Required, exactly 5 digits (French postal code).
.TP
\fBphone\fR
Required, French format (0XXXXXXXXX).
.TP
\fBemail\fR
Optional, standard email format.
.TP
\fBmessage\fR
Required, max 4096 characters.
.TP
\fBg-recaptcha-response\fR
Required, for bot protection.
.SH SECURITY FEATURES
The service includes several security measures:
.RS
.IP \[bu] 2
Input validation prevents injection attacks
.IP \[bu] 2
reCAPTCHA verification blocks automated submissions
.IP \[bu] 2
Rate limiting prevents spam/abuse
.IP \[bu] 2
TLS SMTP ensures secure email transmission
.IP \[bu] 2
Request timeouts prevent DoS attacks
.IP \[bu] 2
Content type restriction to form data only
.RE
.SH SIGNALS
The service responds to the following signals:
.TP
\fBSIGTERM, SIGINT\fR
Gracefully shutdown the service, allowing in-flight requests to complete.
.TP
\fBSIGHUP\fR
Reload configuration (if supported).
.SH FILES
.TP
\fI/etc/gosendmail/config.yaml\fR
Main configuration file.
.TP
\fI/etc/gosendmail/gosendmail.env\fR
Environment variables template.
.TP
\fI/var/log/gosendmail/\fR
Log files directory.
.TP
\fI/run/gosendmail.pid\fR
PID file location.
.SH EXAMPLES
Start the service with default configuration:
.IP
.B gosendmail

Start the service with a custom configuration file:
.IP
.B gosendmail -c /path/to/config.yaml

Check the service health:
.IP
.B curl http://localhost:8080/health

.SH NOTES
This is not the traditional sendmail MTA (Mail Transfer Agent). It's specifically designed to handle web contact form submissions and should not be used as a general-purpose mail transfer agent.
.SH BUGS
Please report bugs to the package maintainer or through the project's issue tracker.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR curl (1),
.BR systemd (1),
.BR smtp (8)

For more information, visit the project documentation or consult the README file included with the package.